---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Resume" description="Dave Lewis — Technical writer résumé with experience, skills, and education.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">

    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="py-24 sm:py-32 flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-start sm:justify-between gap-6">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 mb-3">
          Résumé
        </p>
        <h1 class="font-display text-5xl sm:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-white">
          Dave Lewis
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
          Technical Writer
        </p>
      </div>
      <a
        href="/resume.pdf"
        download
        class="self-start inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-md bg-blue-700 text-white font-medium text-sm hover:bg-blue-800 transition-colors print:hidden"
      >
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/>
          <polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/>
          <line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/>
        </svg>
        Download PDF
      </a>
    </section>

    <!-- Summary -->
    <section class="py-12 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-slate-400 dark:text-slate-500 mb-4">
        Summary
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        Technical writer with experience producing clear, accurate documentation for software products.
        Applies a technical aptitude to grasp new concepts and acquire new skills quickly. 
        Proven track record in implementing and maintaining documentation single-sourcing systems that are reliable, flexible, and cost-effective.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Experience -->
    <section class="py-12 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-slate-400 dark:text-slate-500 mb-6">
        Experience
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-8">

        <div>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between gap-1 mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">
              Senior Technical Writer
            </h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-500 shrink-0">Jun 2024 – Apr 2026</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-2">Alida · Vancouver, BC · Hybrid</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Documented the company's first generative AI assistant and a new suite of modern reporting features, including weighting, significance testing, sentiment analysis, and choice-based conjoint analysis.</li>
            <li>Led the migration of all company documentation from standalone product-specific help sites to a unified set of articles in Zendesk Knowledge.</li>
            <li>Converted tools and processes from XMetaL Author to Oxygen XML Author for direct publishing to Zendesk.</li>
            <li>Built GitHub Actions–based workflows to stage documentation for review outside of Zendesk, to validate all DITA content using Schematron, and to manage Zendesk article redirects.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between gap-1 mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">
              Technical Writer
            </h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-500 shrink-0">Feb 2024 – Jun 2024</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-2">DTL Communications (Client: Telus International) · Vancouver, BC · Remote</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Researched and wrote technical evaluation and implementation documentation for Telus SmartHome+, targeting technical staff at prospective customer service providers.</li>
            <li>Documented the SmartHome+ architecture, which integrates smart home devices — including lights, voice assistants, cameras, and safety sensors — with Amazon Web Services (AWS) for authentication, device connectivity and controls, and AI-powered video processing.</li>
            <li>Reviewed, edited, and wrote developer documentation in the OpenAPI specification for the SmartHome+ API.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between gap-1 mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">
              Senior Technical Writer
            </h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-500 shrink-0">Nov 2020 – Oct 2023</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-2">Alida · Hybrid</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Wrote documentation for administrators and research analysts across a full-featured analytics platform, enterprise administration features, and customer community engagement tools.</li>
            <li>Partnered with Product Management, Engineering, QA, and UX in an agile environment to ship documentation alongside feature releases for a globally distributed product team.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between gap-1 mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">
              Senior Technical Writer
            </h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-500 shrink-0">2017 – Nov 2020</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-2">ActiveState · Vancouver, BC</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Wrote end-user documentation for the ActiveState Platform and Komodo IDE. Generated and maintained documentation for ActiveState's open-source distributions of the Python, Perl, Tcl, Ruby, and Go programming languages.</li>
            <li>Overhauled existing documentation tools and processes. Replaced a homegrown system of custom scripts for each supported programming language with a standard approach for all ActiveState documentation. Implemented a new workflow with Markdown for content, the Hugo static site generator for templating and processing, and GitHub and AWS Amplify for continuous deployment and hosting.</li>
            <li>Supported Product Management, Customer Success, and other teams with data analytics to measure product usage. Also, maintained a visual dashboard with key company metrics.</li>
            <li>Served in a Product Management role on a project to migrate existing customers to the new ActiveState Platform.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Skills -->
    <section class="py-12 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-slate-400 dark:text-slate-500 mb-4">
        Skills
      </h2>
      <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        {[
          'API documentation', 'Developer guides', 'User manuals',
          'OpenAPI / Swagger', 'DITA', 'Markdown / MDX',
          'Docs-as-code', 'Git', 'Content strategy',
          'Structured authoring', 'HTML / CSS',
        ].map((skill) => (
          <li class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            {skill}
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Education -->
    <section class="py-12 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-slate-400 dark:text-slate-500 mb-6">
        Education
      </h2>
      <div>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between gap-1 mb-1">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">
            Bachelor of Arts (B.A.), English
          </h3>
          <span class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-500 shrink-0">1997–2000</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">Simon Fraser University · Burnaby, British Columbia</p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  @media print {
    nav, footer { display: none; }
    section { page-break-inside: avoid; }
  }
</style>
